project: The day is gloomy as people gather in the square. You close your eyes against the wind, then open them again to pay attention.

Executioner: You have all been gathered here today to bear witness to the death of this monster, a killer of innumerable unfortunate families and individuals. Any who oppose this execution may speak now, or forever hold your peace.
The executioner turns to you inquisitively.
EXECUTIONER: Very well, then. The execution shall commence.
They pull the lever for the electric chair. You grit your teeth against the pain, holding your breath.
YOU: What? Get away from me!
GRIM: You will not last long without a guide.
YOU: What do I need a guide for?
GRIM: I am the only guest of the damned that can speak sinner language.
YOU: What language do the others speak?
YOU: Riddles? What kind of riddles?

GRIM: I can share with you a riddle of mine, as long as you are aware that the prose of the damned is to be answered with a correct response, and if that condition is not fulfilled, the asker shall fly into a rage and attack you. However, answering a riddle respectfully and correctly is flattering to most.
YOU: Ominous… give me your riddle.
GRIM: What can run but never walks, has a mouth but never talks, has a head but never weeps, has a bed but never sleeps?
Grim: Wrong. The correct answer is: A river. Another guest of the damned would kill you for this mistake.
you: I thought my answer sounded about right, but fine.
Grim: Correct. Though a famous riddle, it is pleasing to hear the song of a correct answer from a sinner.
You: We tell that riddle on Earth, too. Didn’t expect knowing it would be helpful in the afterlife.
Grim: Very well, but you cannot answer so disrespectfully in response to a real riddle; you would be struck down posthaste.
YOU: So… What happens if I answer too many riddles wrong?
GRIM: Your Afterlife Force will diminish with any damage taken to your soul, until it is irreparable and you are lost to even Damnation.
YOU: …Oh. Well– riddles aside, what do I do now? Where are we going?
YOU: …Oh. Well– riddles aside, what do I do now? Where are we going?
Thanks for playing our demo!!!! We will make more parts soon. This was made in one week.
